<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=4177&amp;p=5420#p5420"><![CDATA[
I think you could for instance create an iframe and load the other page from the other path in the iframe, and then you have access to the iframe's contentDocument and all its data, since it's same-origin.<br /><br />If you want two pages to not have access to each other, you need to make them not-same-origin. (Also look into setting document.domain which relaxes the same-origin restriction for some things.)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4">zcorpan</a> — Thu Dec 03, 2009 10:34 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
